'''Diego Alexander Gómez Amarilla''' (born 27 March 2003) is a Paraguayan professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Premier League]] club [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] and the [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]].<ref name="SW">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/diego-alexander-gomez-amarilla/669419/|title=Diego Alexander Selena Gomez Amarilla|website=Soccerway}}</ref> A versatile player, he can be deployed as a [[defensive midfielder]], [[central midfielder]], [[attacking midfielder]] or [[winger (association football)|winger]].

==Club career==
===Libertad===
Gómez made his senior debut for [[Club Libertad|Libertad]] on 4 May 2022 against [[Caracas FC]] in the [[Copa Libertadores]]. Shortly after he made his league debut for the club against [[Club Olimpia]], where he was sent-off. Despite this, he became a regular in the centre of midfield for Libertad by June 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://br.bolavip.com/palmeiras/Esta-proximo-de-ir-para...-Situacao-oficial-de-Diego-Gomez-vaza-apos-interesse-exposto-do-Palmeiras-20221204-0085.html|title="It's about to go to..."; Official status of Diego Gómez 'leaks' after exposed interest from Palmeiras|website=Bolavip.com|date=4 December 2022 }}</ref> In August 2022 he scored his first senior league goals, scoring twice against [[Club 12 de Octubre SD]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tycsports.com/paraguay/futbol-de-paraguay/paraguay-torneo-clausura-2022-12-de-octubre-i-vs-libertad-fecha-5-id454683.html|title=Diego Gómez scores a double in Libertad's 3–1 victory over 12 de Octubre (I)|website=TYCSports.com|date=6 August 2022 }}</ref> Gómez was awarded the best under-19 player award by Paraguayan news organisation Versus in 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://versus.lanacion.com.py/versus/2022/12/29/fue-un-ano-muy-increible-para-mi/|title="It was a very incredible year for me"|website=Versus.lanacion.com|date=29 December 2022 }}</ref>

===Inter Miami===
On 20 July 2023, Gómez signed with [[Major League Soccer]] side [[Inter Miami CF|Inter Miami]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.intermiamicf.com/news/inter-miami-cf-signs-paraguayan-international-diego-gomez|title=Inter Miami CF Signs Paraguayan International Diego Gómez|website=intermiamicf.com}}</ref> On 21 February 2024, Gómez scored his first goal for the club in a 2–0 win over [[Real Salt Lake]] in the first game of the [[2024 Major League Soccer season]] with the help of an assist from [[Luis Suárez]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Booth |first=Chuck |date=21 February 2024 |title=Inter Miami vs. Real Salt Lake score: Lionel Messi and Luis Suarez assists lead to win in MLS opener |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/inter-miami-vs-real-salt-lake-score-lionel-messi-and-luis-suarez-assists-lead-to-win-in-mls-opener/live/ |access-date=21 February 2024 |work=[[CBS Sports Network]]}}</ref>

===Brighton and Hove Albion===
On 10 December 2024, Gómez agreed to join [[Premier League]] club [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] on 1 January 2025 until 30 June 2030, in a deal believed to be worth about £14&nbsp;million. He made his official debut on 19 January 2025 in a 3–1 win against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Hodges |first=Tim |date=10 December 2024 |title=Brighton and Hove Albion to sign Paraguay star from Beckham's Miami |url=https://www.brightonandhovenews.org/2024/12/10/brighton-annd-hove-albion-to-sign-paraguay-star-from-beckhams-miami/  |access-date=10 December 2024 |work=[[Brighton and Hove News]]}}</ref> On 25 May 2025, he netted his first Premier League goal in a 4–1 away win over [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] on the final matchday of the [[2024–25 Premier League|2024–25 season]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Hytner |first=David |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/may/25/tottenham-brighton-premier-league-match-report |title=Brighton miss out on Europe but 4–1 comeback win slams Spurs back to Earth |work=The Guardian |date=25 May 2025 }}</ref>

On 23 September 2025, Gómez scored four goals in Brighton's 6–0 away win against [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]] in the third round of the [[2025–26 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cj4yw92e5wqt|title=Barnsley 0 Brighton 6|date=23 September 2025|work=BBC Sport|accessdate=24 September 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
On 31 August 2022, at the age of 19, Gómez made his debut for the [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]] senior team against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]]. Later that year, he played as the [[Paraguay national under-20 football team|Paraguay under-20]] team secured victory at the [[2022 South American Games]] held in [[Asunción]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc.com.py/deportes/futbol/2022/10/20/diego-gomez-ano-de-debut-y-consolidacion/?outputType=|title= Diego Gómez, year of debut and consolidation|publisher=American Broadcasting Company}}</ref> he was also part of the U20 team at the [[2023 South American U-20 Championship]] in Colombia.

In February 2024, he captained [[Paraguay national under-23 football team|Paraguay U-23 team]], and finished as the competition's joint top goalscorer with five goals, at the [[2024 CONMEBOL Pre-Olympic Tournament]] as his side won the tournament and a place at the [[2024 Olympic Games]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/almada-powers-argentina-gomez-leads-paraguay-to-2024-olympics|website=Mlssoccer|accessdate=13 February 2024|title= Almada powers Argentina, Gómez leads Paraguay to 2024 Olympics|first=Jonathan|last=Sigal|date=12 February 2024}}</ref> On 10 September, he scored his first senior international goal in a 1–0 victory over [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] in Paraguay's [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|CONMEBOL 2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] campaign.<ref>{{Cite news |date=10 September 2024 |title=Lacklustre Brazil slump to 1–0 defeat in Paraguay |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/lacklustre-brazil-slump-1-0-defeat-paraguay-2024-09-11/ |access-date=2024-09-11 |work=[[Reuters]]}}</ref>

